The paper discusses a technique for identifying malicious traffic flows in IoT networks, which falls under the category of network security. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of network traffic analysis and machine learning algorithms, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses feature selection and fuzzy clustering techniques, which are related to sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
